<HEADLINE>
NUMBER OF VISITORS HITS NEW HIGH IN 2006
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  March 2 (CNA) 03/02/07  22:53:55 (By Y.C. Jou)
</P>
<P>
The number of foreigners visiting Taiwan hit a new high last
year, reaching 3.52 million individual entries, tourism
authorities said Friday.
</P>
<P>
According to tallies of the Tourism Bureau under the Ministry of
Transportation and Communications, there were 3,519,827 instances
of foreign visitors entering Taiwan in 2006; a four percent
increase compared to the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Of these visitors, the largest group were Japanese, accounting
for around 31 percent, followed by persons from Hong Kong and
Macao, then America.
</P>
<P>
At a Tourism Day celebration event Friday, Premier Su Tseng-chang
honored individuals in the tourism industry with special
achievements and promoted the government's Doubling Tourists
Arrival Plan, which aims to increase the number of visitors
annually to 5 million entries, 2 million of which should be
tourists, by the end of 2008.
</P>
